</p>


<h4>Software distributions</h4>

<p>
gtk-gnutella is available from several software distributions.
</p>

<h5>Linux</h5>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://packages.ubuntu.com/search?keywords=gtk-gnutella">Ubuntu</a></li>
<li><a href="http://packages.gentoo.org/package/net-p2p/gtk-gnutella">Gentoo</a></li>
<li><a href="http://packages.debian.org/search?keywords=gtk-gnutella">Debian</a></li>
<li><a href="http://rpmfind.net/linux/rpm2html/search.php?query=gtk-gnutella">Fedora</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.archlinux.de/?page=Packages&amp;search=gtk-gnutella">Arch Linux</a></li>
</ul>

<h5>BSD</h5>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://pkgsrc.se/net/gtk-gnutella">pkgsrc - The NetBSD package collection</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.freshports.org/net-p2p/gtk-gnutella/">FreshPorts - FreeBSD packages</a></li>
<li><a href="http://openports.se/net/gtk-gnutella">openports - The OpenBSD package collection</a></li>
</ul>

<h5>Darwin (Mac OS X)</h5>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://gtk-gnutella.darwinports.com/">Darwin Ports</a></li>
<li><a href="http://pdb.finkproject.org/pdb/package.php/gtk-gnutella">Fink</a></li>
</ul>

<p>
These are the most convenient options for installing gtk-gnutella but the
provided version of gtk-gnutella may be outdated.
</p>

<h4>Unofficial builds</h4>

<p>
Joel Oliver provides unofficial builds for several Linux-based software
distributions for x86 (32-bit) and x86-64/amd64 (64-bit) systems. His builds
are compiled from recent SVN sources and updated frequently:
</p>

<p>
<a href="http://stinker.serveftp.net:8000/gtkgnutella/gtkgnutella.html"
>http://stinker.serveftp.net:8000/gtkgnutella/gtkgnutella.html</a>
</p>

<p>
Please, report any bugs and problems with gtk-gnutella at our
<a href="?page=mailing">mailing lists</a> or <a href="?page=bugreport_howto">bug tracker</a>!
</p>

